Business Brief -- RJR Nabisco Inc.:
   Construction Is Begun
   On Facility in Turkey
A Reynolds spokeswoman said Turkey consumes about 83
billion cigarettes a year, a rate growing at about 1% to 2%
annually. The Turkish government opened the country's tobacco
industry to private-sector investment in May.
   Philip Morris Cos.' international tobacco unit currently
markets Turkey's No. 1 and No. 2 brands, Marlboro and
Parliament, respectively, through its Turkish joint venture
known as Philsa.